<br>
There seem to be a lot more newbies begging for stuff, and really having no clue. To keep that in perspective though, maybe they were always there, I just a) had nothing they needed and b) didn't know enough myself to realize they knew even less than me. <br>
<br>
I came from Vazaelle way back when and have never regretted it. I started in Everfrost, and was treated very well. I never asked for anything other than maybe a sow until level 9, but I was the beneficiary of many buffs and trinkets that probably didn't mean as much to my benefactors as they did me. I used my Runed Totem Staff for around 15 levels <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
There will probably always be those who mooch, but the kindness that was shown to me in a very tough newbie zone has made me the player I am today. I try to give back to those I think really need my help, and I hope one day, they continue the circle. <br>
<br>
Quellious is a good server, with a lot of talented players and good people. We are far from perfect, but I think in small ways, all of us are trying to do better. Each time we avoid senseless conflicts such as those brought to the boards, we are one step closer to realizing our potential as a community and not just a server.<br>
