<br>
SO people get bored and sell their characters or sometimes give them away, and you get 'new' people coming in that don't know the game and have no sense of community, they usually leave their current guild and try to guildhop. Fail to get into the big leagues because they know crap.(usually fail but I know exceptions) Then having hit the glass ceiling like their predecessor they move on too. But not before getting bitter and pissing a few people off on the way, and generally making Quellious a lesser place.<br>
<br>
Eventually EQ2 will come out or some other game that competes well and everyone will leave but the people who are actually getting to see all the content they want, and it'll be fine. No one will be bitter.<br>
<br>
The problem isn't the guilds. Or the people. If getting your epic was a challenge for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> you</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or your guild it would be different.<br>
<br>
But things like Ragefire can do nothing BUT cause animosity. This game should NOT pit players against players in this fashion, it ruins the game. It ruins the community. It takes the fun out of it and turns toons into unskilled and uncivilized  dopplegangers of themselves. (when they quit and someone else gets the account)<br>
<br>
Impossible you say? Not at all. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> One</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> solution would be for epic fights to be 'cage of death' type fights. You do a turn in now you and your group (who must be your level or lower)are in a fight alone with the mob that can have no interference form anyone else. You fail you start over and try again maybe in a level or two. Then if you see a lvl 52 with an epic it MEANS something. Anyway that's just one idea, I am sure if I spent an hour I could think of a half dozen more, but the current system of pitting people against people in THIS manner is very very destructive to the game.<br>
<br>
I'd rather FIGHT other people literally for something than the way it is. At least there would be a real conflict you could get your teeth into. Strip the clerics naked, give them summonned gear, and let them pvp for the damn thing would be BETTER than what happens now.<br>
<br>
Anyway, my .02cp<br>
<br>
